# Voice and Knowledge Guardrails

- Treat speech providers as pluggable capabilities; do not hardcode a single STT/TTS vendor.
- Keep premium voice options explicit and configurable per agent (`voice_profile`, `speech_profile`).
- Realtime voice pipelines should degrade gracefully if provider credentials are missing.
- Ingestion flows must write normalized source records (`agent_knowledge_sources`) before pushing content into KB documents.
- For URL/sitemap ingestion, sanitize and limit fetched text size before embedding.
- Avoid storing PII-heavy raw transcripts in logs; summarize and persist only what is needed for support/reporting workflows.
